│ 687   ///  2) In worst case, it increases the complexity from O(N*I) to                                                                                                                                        │
│ 688   ///     O(2*N*I), where N is # of Instructions to merge, and I is the                                                                                                                                    │
│ 689   ///     maximum level of inline stack. So it is still linear.                                                                                                                                            │
│ 690   ///  3) Merging of call instructions should be extremely rare in real                                                                                                                                    │
│ 691   ///     applications, thus the N-way merging should be in code path.                                                                                                                                     │
